text: Kern Valley High School is a small high school in Lake Isabella, California. It is one of the high schools in the Kern High School District. The school has a staff of about 80 teachers and support staff, and about 484 students. == References == Category:1941 establishments Category:1941 establishments in California Category:1941 establishments in the United States Category:High schools in the United States Category:Schools in California
